FBIS4-37957 "drnes123_j_94014" FBIS-NES-94-123 Daily Report 27 Jun 1994 Arabian Peninsula Further Reportage on Fighting Around Aden Further Reportage on Fighting Around Aden South Takes Losses in Bid To Repulse North NC2706074594 Paris AFP in English 0730 GMT 27 Jun 94 NC2706074594 Paris AFP English BFN [Text] Aden, Yemen, June 27 (AFP) -- At least eight southern Yemeni soldiers were killed and 69 wounded on Monday [27 June] in a battle to repulse a northern advance into Aden's western suburbs, hospital officials said. Southern artillery gunners pounded northern forces in a bid to dislodge them from positions around the power station at Hiswah and Aden Radio station, about 10 kilometers (six miles) west of the city.
